 The event, Rusty Summer Fiesta, was held in December last year.One of the event organisers, Success Shondli, said the Lenyora hitmaker accepted the deposit but failed to pitch for the gumba without giving any reasons."We had agreed on a fee of R40000 for his performance. We paid him half the amount and the balance was supposed to be paid after he performed, but he did not pitch on the day of the show," said Shondli.TO READ THE FULL STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD AT YOUR NEAREST STORE